race.comment: SIMPLY EXCELS (8) loves this distance range with two wins and two placings from just five attempts and will be ready to peak now third-up from the break. Gets the deadly Gollan/Maloney combination and should be in this contest for a long way. Former Victorian CENTENNIAL PARK (5) resumes here for the new stable but the form he showed in his first preparation was good enough for a race of this calibre. Makes plenty of appeal while fresh. THANKYOU HENRY (3) has placed three of four over this trip, strips fitter third-up and draws the inside marble. Ticks a few boxes. PARETO (1) was a touch flat last time out but the form prior was full of merit. Worth another chance with the 3kg claim. The well-related NEGOTIATIONS (4) (half to G2 winner Hidden Motive) best of the rest.
